CamTCC1137.First Lines: Thys booke hyȝt ypocrasoon of þe beste surgens þat euer was…
CamTCC1137.Last Lines: …Pray we for all to heuene kyngeHe ȝeue her soulys goode wonyngw
CamTCC1137.Note: Stands alone, not as an introduction or epilogue; written two lines of verse per line in the manuscript except last two lines written as separate lines; ends “Amen ffinitus medicinis incipit hic liber coquinare,” but remainder of leaf blank.
